**********************************************************************
MAUI Mailbox Information demo code
**********************************************************************
What this demo does:
  - The demo prints information about mailboxes in memory. It has command 
    line options to either "dump" the content of the mailbox on the sceen 
    or decode messages, stored in the mailbox.

**********************************************************************
System requirements:
  - A working MAUI environment is assumed.
 
**********************************************************************
Directories: 
  - Source code 
      $MWOS/SRC/MAUI/DEMOS/MSGINFO
        
**********************************************************************
To make this demo:
  - From the source file directory type:
      % os9make
 
**********************************************************************
Operation:
 
  - This demo has several command line options. Run it with -h or -? 
    option to find out what options are supported. "-d" option dumps 
    the mailbox content on the sceen, "-dd" attempts to decode 
    messages in the mailbox. For example:

      $ msginfo -d <mbox1> <mbox2> ...

**********************************************************************
 
